## The Reality Check: Revenue & Making a Living

<blockquote class="relative border-l-4 border-error pl-6 my-8 italic text-lg text-base-content/80">
  <span class="absolute -left-3 -top-2 text-5xl text-error/20">"</span>
  We don't really do this to sell as much as possible. We do it more for fun... it's nice to work with family and to have like a project together.
</blockquote>

### The Honest Numbers

Let's be real here. Erik works in IT, Mark helps young people with mental health. Bitcoin Design is their side project, and they're not pretending otherwise.

**Sales after 5 years:** 30-40 pieces total.

That's not a typo. They're not moving thousands of units. They're making art, piece by piece, while working full-time jobs.

### Why Keep the Day Job?

- **Bitcoin markets are cyclical** - "Sometimes nobody is interested, then everyone is enthusiastic"
- **It's about family and fun**, not maximizing profits
- **They want balance, not burnout** - Started in 2020, they've seen the waves
- **Erik's ideal future?** Work one less day at the job, one more day making art with his brother

That's it. No "we're going to disrupt the art world" bullshit.

### What They Actually Sell

**Product range:**
- Bronze sculptures in three sizes (desk, medium, XXL)
- Glass pieces with melted glass Bitcoin art (more hand work, less material cost)
- Custom engravings like the date someone bought their first Bitcoin

**Where sales happen:**
- Mostly at exhibitions where people can feel the weight
- Some online (though most clients are still Dutch)
- Conference organizers keep inviting them for free (only sculptors in a sea of paintings)

### The Copyright Advantage Nobody Talks About

<blockquote class="relative border-l-4 border-success pl-6 my-8 italic text-lg text-base-content/80">
  <span class="absolute -left-3 -top-2 text-5xl text-success/20">"</span>
  Because it's decentralized, we can make this statue actually. Otherwise, there were a lot of... there's no copyright. So that's the good part.
</blockquote>

Bitcoin's logo has no copyright. No licensing fees. No lawyers. No cease and desist letters.

You want to cast a 10kg bronze Bitcoin? Go ahead. Nobody owns it. That's the point.

